00:19:06,258 --> 00:19:09,159
''Now, the boundaries
of our village are:''

267
00:19:09,228 --> 00:19:13,164
''To the east, the bridge.
To the west, the old kirk road.''

268
00:19:13,232 --> 00:19:16,565
''To the north, the stone fence
at the edge of the forest...''

269
00:19:16,635 --> 00:19:19,229
''and to the south, Loch Harold.''

270
00:19:19,305 --> 00:19:20,738
Let no one cross...

271
00:19:20,806 --> 00:19:24,242
or we shall be ungrateful
before God...

272
00:19:24,310 --> 00:19:27,279
and night shall
fall upon us forever.

273
00:19:34,820 --> 00:19:38,756
The second day of whose blessin'?
'Tis for certain not mine.

274
00:19:38,824 --> 00:19:41,292
-l'm truly sorry.
-Do not be.

275
00:19:41,360 --> 00:19:44,090
''lf anyone's goin' to pity me,
let it be me.''

276
00:19:44,163 --> 00:19:47,462
'Tis not fair for Charlie Dalrymple
to be weddin' her.

277
00:19:47,533 --> 00:19:50,798
