where we could find a local inn?

286
00:20:54,667 --> 00:20:56,134
What is this?

287
00:20:58,871 --> 00:21:01,806
ls there a place around here
where we could get some breakfast?

288
00:21:01,874 --> 00:21:05,275
''-l do not know, sir.
-What do you know? lt talks.''

289
00:21:05,344 --> 00:21:07,278
What's the name of this town?

290
00:21:08,380 --> 00:21:10,814
l do not know.
You'll have to excuse me.

291
00:21:13,786 --> 00:21:15,253
You're in Brigadoon.

292
00:21:22,995 --> 00:21:24,929
-Good morning.
-Good morning.

293
00:21:24,997 --> 00:21:28,455
You must forgive him. l imagine
he was a wee bit taken back.

294
00:21:28,534 --> 00:21:30,525
People do not come here
very often.

295
00:21:31,704 --> 00:21:33,934
What did you say
the name of this town is?

296
00:21:34,006 --> 00:21:35,303
Brigadoon.

297
00:21:36,375 --> 00:21:38,309
That's funny.
lt isn't on the map.

298
00:21:38,377 --> 00:21:39,935
l should not be surprised.

299
00:21:40,012 --> 00:21:41,946
You know it isn't on the map?

300
00:21:42,014 --> 00:21:43,276
Aye.

301
00:21:43,349 --> 00:21:45,510
''That's a little snobbish of you,
don't you think?''

302
00:21:47,252 --> 00:21:50,244
-Why isn't it on the map?
-For good reason.

303
00:21:52,291 --> 00:21:54,657
''Well, look, Miss, uh--''

304
00:21:54,727 --> 00:21:57,161
-Campbell.
-Thank you.

305
00:21:57,229 --> 00:22:01,666
We're trying to get some breakfast.
ls there an inn around here?

306
00:22:01,734 --> 00:22:03,668
An inn?
l do not think so.

307
00:22:03,736 --> 00:22:06,432
''But if you follow the road,
you'll come to MacConnachy Square.''

308
00:22:06,505 --> 00:22:08,666
You can find all the food you want
for sale there.

309
00:22:09,808 --> 00:22:11,639
