something peculiar about you.

321
00:23:40,799 --> 00:23:43,495
''This milk is for sale,
isn't it?''

322
00:23:43,569 --> 00:23:45,560
-Aye.
-Do you mind if l help myself?

323
00:23:45,637 --> 00:23:49,300
''One moment, sir.
l'll have to see your money first.''

324
00:23:49,374 --> 00:23:51,308
-My money?
-Show 'im the money.

325
00:23:58,650 --> 00:24:00,811
-Look at the date!
-Funny-lookin' thing.

326
00:24:00,886 --> 00:24:03,013
What did you give 'em?
A hunk of uranium?

327
00:24:03,088 --> 00:24:06,353
''No, just a shilling.
What a loony layout this is.''

328
00:24:07,359 --> 00:24:09,827
''Aye, 'tis very interesting, sir...''

329
00:24:09,895 --> 00:24:11,692
but it does me no good.

330
00:24:11,764 --> 00:24:13,857
You mean you won't sell me anything?

331
00:24:13,932 --> 00:24:16,958
''l'm sorry, sir. l cannot.''

332
00:24:17,035 --> 00:24:18,297
Why not?

333
00:24:18,370 --> 00:24:20,338
''l cannot explain further, sir.''

334
00:24:22,508 --> 00:24:24,442
They just happened in
a wee while ago.

335
00:24:26,512 --> 00:24:29,879
''Well, welcome to Brigadoon.
How did you gentlemen get here?''

336
00:24:29,948 --> 00:24:32,712
''We came from Graymore,
six miles yonder.''

337
00:24:32,785 --> 00:24:34,912
Six miles.
That's quite a distance.

338
00:24:34,987 --> 00:24:38,354
''You must be hungry. Angus, how about
some breakfast for our visitors?''

339
00:24:38,423 --> 00:24:40,653
''Charlie, their money--''

340
00:24:40,726 --> 00:24:42,523
l do not want their money.

341
00:24:42,594 --> 00:24:45,427
''This is my weddin' day, laddie.
You're my invited guests.''

342
00:24:45,497 --> 00:24:49,433
''Help yourselves.
Bread, scones, ginger cakes.''

343
00:24:49,501 --> 00:24:52,470
''Oh, but first,
a bit o' heather ale.''

344
00:24:54,106 --> 00:24:55,164
Sandy!

345
00:24:56,074 --> 00:24:58,133
-Here l am.
-Some ale for our guests.

346
00:24:59,745 --> 00:25:01,235
Ale for everybody!

347
00:25:07,019 --> 00:25:09,351
So you're getting married today.
That's wonderful.

348
00:25:09,421 --> 00:25:11,082
''Aye, it is.''

349
00:25:11,156 --> 00:25:13,647
''This afternoon,
to Miss Jean Campbell.''

350
00:25:13,725 --> 00:25:15,659
-Campbell?
-Aye.

351
00:25:17,162 --> 00:25:21,189
l think l met your bride
a few minutes ago. She's very charming.

352
00:25:21,266 --> 00:25:23,734
''Aye, that she is.''

353
00:25:23,802 --> 00:25:25,770
Her health.
Her health!

354
00:25:28,841 --> 00:25:31,401
-To our visitors!
-Here!

355
00:25:31,476 --> 00:25:33,239
