You should be gettin' ready.

571
00:45:01,078 --> 00:45:02,875
l was waitin' for Fiona.

572
00:45:02,947 --> 00:45:05,472
Where is she?
She's been gone for hours.

573
00:45:07,385 --> 00:45:10,821
Go to your room.
Close the door.

574
00:45:10,888 --> 00:45:12,822
''Charlie, go 'round to the window.''

575
00:45:20,064 --> 00:45:21,326
Here's the Bible.

576
00:45:21,399 --> 00:45:22,991
There's the quill and ink.

577
00:45:23,067 --> 00:45:26,036
Now sit ye down there and sign
right under the name...

578
00:45:26,103 --> 00:45:28,264
of my dear departed wife.

579
00:45:28,339 --> 00:45:30,830
''And when you've done that,
take your leave!''

580
00:45:30,908 --> 00:45:32,205
''Aye, sir.''

581
00:46:00,371 --> 00:46:03,499
This is where l come all day
and tend my flock.

582
00:46:03,574 --> 00:46:06,509
''When l say it sounds fascinating,
l want you to believe me.''

583
00:46:10,247 --> 00:46:13,375
-lt's a very picturesque view.
-Thank ya.

584
00:46:13,451 --> 00:46:16,215
-What for?
-For likin' where l've brought ya.

585
00:46:16,287 --> 00:46:18,346
lt makes me very happy.

586
00:46:18,422 --> 00:46:20,913
''-You get happy very easily, don't you?
-Aye.''

587
00:46:23,494 --> 00:46:27,089
l haven't been in a shed like this
since l was in college...

588
00:46:27,164 --> 00:46:30,133
''which at this point seems
a good 2,000 years ago.''

589
00:46:30,201 --> 00:46:33,261
''-Ya mean you're tired?
-Aye, lassie, l'm tired.''

590
00:46:33,337 --> 00:46:36,272
''That's what you brought me here for,
wasn't it, so l could take a nap?''

591
00:46:36,340 --> 00:46:39,935
l should not think a long walk
would fatigue a young lad like ye.

592
00:46:40,010 --> 00:46:42,535
''-A young lad?
-Aye, you're very young.''

593
00:46:42,613 --> 00:46:45,377
That's either a deliberate lie
or wishful thinking.

594
00:46:45,449 --> 00:46:48,816
''l am ancient, decrepit
and disintegrating rapidly.''

595
00:46:48,886 --> 00:46:51,286
My mother and father
met in this shed.

596
00:46:51,355 --> 00:46:53,050
We all make mistakes.

597
00:46:53,124 --> 00:46:54,819
My mother was a gypsy...

598
00:46:54,892 --> 00:46:56,860
and one day she was
walkin' past this shed...

599
00:46:56,927 --> 00:46:59,623
and she saw my father
lyin' down asleep.

600
00:46:59,697 --> 00:47:03,224
''She liked his looks,
and she was achin' for a husband.''

601
00:47:03,300 --> 00:47:07,293
''So, she took off her shoes,
sat in the rocking chair there...''

602
00:47:07,371 --> 00:47:09,601
and waited for him to wake up.

603
00:47:09,673 --> 00:47:12,369
And it was not long after that
that l was born.

604
00:47:12,443 --> 00:47:15,503
That's one of the sweetest
bedtime stories l've ever heard.

605
00:47:17,815 --> 00:47:19,874
''What's under here, your father?''

606
00:47:22,620 --> 00:47:25,555
Thank you very much.
You've been more than kind.

607
00:47:25,623 --> 00:47:28,751
''Now, if you want to round out
your generosity, buzz off.''

608
00:47:28,826 --> 00:47:30,885
l just hate to leave ya.

609
00:47:30,961 --> 00:47:34,863
''You better. When l sleep,
l make all sorts of odd noises.''

610
00:47:34,932 --> 00:47:37,400
Who told ya?
Ya do not have a wife.

611
00:47:37,468 --> 00:47:38,958
l was engaged once.

612
00:47:39,036 --> 00:47:41,732
You're a right winnin' lad.

613
00:47:41,805 --> 00:47:43,739
You should have someone
to take care of ya.

614
00:47:43,807 --> 00:47:47,243
l don't know what you're after.
l just wanna go to sleep.

615
00:47:47,311 --> 00:47:48,573
Now go!

616
00:47:50,814 --> 00:47:52,076
Go?

617
00:47:53,083 --> 00:47:57,179
But do ya not see?
l'm highly attracted to ya.

618
00:47:57,254 --> 00:48:01,384
''Why, when l look at ya, l feel
wee tadpoles jumpin' in my spine.''

619
00:48:01,458 --> 00:48:04,950
That's about as repulsive an idea
as l've heard in years.

620
00:48:05,029 --> 00:48:08,157
''lf love were a hobby,
you'd be a collector's item.''

621
00:48:08,232 --> 00:48:10,257
All you men are all alike.

622
00:48:10,334 --> 00:48:12,894
-l should certainly hope so.
-You're all brutes!

623
00:48:12,970 --> 00:48:15,734
Ya get what ya want from a lass
an' then 'tis farewell!

624
00:48:15,806 --> 00:48:18,240
Get what l want?
l can't even get you to go away!

625
00:48:18,309 --> 00:48:20,072
That's what l'm referrin' to.

626
00:48:20,144 --> 00:48:23,580
l thought ya wanted to propose to me.
That's why ya brought me here.

627
00:48:24,949 --> 00:48:26,678
You misled me.

628
00:48:26,750 --> 00:48:29,913
You sure have one lulu
of an imagination.

629
00:48:29,987 --> 00:48:33,047
''Can you think of one good reason
why l, a strange man...''

630
00:48:33,123 --> 00:48:36,058
''should be interested in proposing
to you, a mighty strange woman...''

631
00:48:36,126 --> 00:48:37,753
and at this hour of the day?

632
00:48:37,828 --> 00:48:40,695
''Because you're a lad,
and l'm a lass.''

633
00:48:40,764 --> 00:48:43,892
''With that philosophy, you must have
had a provocative career.''

634
00:48:43,968 --> 00:48:46,835
Now go. Be off.
Away with ya.

635
00:48:46,904 --> 00:48:49,839
-But--
-Go tend your flock.

636
00:49:49,133 --> 00:49:51,431
''Fiona! There's some white heather,
lots of it.''

637
